Movie Ticket PricePrediction¶

Statsly Analytics¶

By Moumita Das¶

Problem Statement¶

With the expansion of OTT platforms like Netflix, Amazon Prime, people prefer to watch content at theirconvenience. Factors like Pricing, Content Quality & Marketing have influenced the success of these platforms. The cost of making a full-length movie has shot up exponentially in the recent past. Only 10% of the movies thatare made make profits. Stiff competition from Television & OTT platforms along with the high ticket cost hasmade it difficult for films to make money even harder. The rising cost of the theatre ticket (along with thepopcorn cost) leaves the cinema hall empty. A movie ticket pricing prediction using Machine Learning can definitely help the movie makers and viewers.Ticket prices can be higher with the rise in demand for tickets and vice versa. The earlier the viewer books theticket, the lesser the cost, for a movie with high demand. Build a Machine Learning model that should smartlycalculate the pricing depending on the interest of the viewers, social signals,supply-demand factors, etc.

Data Preprocessing¶

In [59]:
cols_to_drop = ["occu_perc","capacity","date"]
df = Ticket.drop(columns=cols_to_drop,axis=1)
In [60]:
correlations = df.corr()['ticket_price'].drop('ticket_price')

def get_features(correlation_threshold):
    abs_corrs = correlations.abs()
    high_correlations = abs_corrs[abs_corrs > correlation_threshold].index.values.tolist()
    return high_correlations
In [61]:
features = get_features(0.05)
print(features)

['film_code', 'total_sales', 'tickets_sold', 'show_time', 'ticket_use']
In [62]:
